WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:20.229 --> 00:00:22.148
In 1998. a growable neurochip
was made at Harima Science City.

3
00:00:22.231 --> 00:00:23.524
Its cells are dying
due to excessive growth.

4
00:00:23.607 --> 00:00:25.276
The fibers have grown to terminals
composed of galactose-infused polystyrene

5
00:00:25.359 --> 00:00:27.320
derivatives. distorting the thin
membrane the terminals are printed on.

6
00:00:27.403 --> 00:00:29.656
That same month. cyberbrain technology
begins shifting to a micromachine base.

7
00:00:29.739 --> 00:00:31.699
In 2028. neurochips are widely
used in robots and AIs.

8
00:00:32.324 --> 00:00:34.077
In the near future. electrons and light
race back and forth

9
00:00:34.160 --> 00:00:35.703
through corporate nets
that blanket the globe.

10
00:00:35.786 --> 00:00:37.538
but the notions of nationality
and ethnicity still cling to life

11
00:00:37.621 --> 00:00:38.706
despite the spread of technology.

12
00:00:38.789 --> 00:00:41.250
A strange corporate collective state
lying in a corner of Asia…

13
00:00:41.333 --> 00:00:42.460
Japan Nihon. Nippon
Island nation located in East Asia.

14
00:00:42.543 --> 00:00:43.961
Total area. 377.815 square km.
Total population. 76 million (as of 2029).

15
00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:44.837
MARCH 5. 2029

16
00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:48.070
NIIHAMA PREFECTURE ARTIFICIAL ISLAND
METROPOLIS OF NEWPORT CITY

17
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:55.097
Why the sudden interest
in silicon deposits?

18
00:00:57.057 --> 00:01:00.895
It's important enough that it will
guarantee that my government

19
00:01:00.978 --> 00:01:04.941
will stay out of your country's official
policy of not recognizing secessionists.

20
00:01:05.024 --> 00:01:09.821
Our stated position is that we provide aid
once independence is recognized.

21
00:01:09.904 --> 00:01:12.654
so this will not conflict
with our own trade interests.

22
00:01:13.115 --> 00:01:15.659
We will work through
a third-party country.

23
00:01:18.454 --> 00:01:21.332
Excellent. After all. if a slave state
is negligent in its service.

24
00:01:21.415 --> 00:01:24.127
the master country will starve.

25
00:01:24.210 --> 00:01:27.610
Our manpower shortage will really give
the slave trade a huge boost.

26
00:01:27.838 --> 00:01:31.050
This does deviate somewhat from
our socialist ideals. I must admit.

27
00:01:31.133 --> 00:01:34.721
Despite all your country's
protestations of being capitalists.

28
00:01:34.804 --> 00:01:37.807
the truth is that you're
the ideal socialist state!

29
00:01:40.309 --> 00:01:41.602
What's keeping Team 2?!

30
00:01:43.604 --> 00:01:45.106
Is it the union again?

31
00:01:45.189 --> 00:01:47.525
They say there's been a bomb threat!

32
00:01:47.608 --> 00:01:49.858
We've finished evacuating
the civilians. sir.

33
00:01:53.989 --> 00:01:56.951
Major. Public Security is ready to go.

34
00:01:57.284 --> 00:01:59.871
I know. for crying out loud…

35
00:01:59.954 --> 00:02:02.081
When you let an AI
handle the encryption.

36
00:02:02.164 --> 00:02:04.764
everyone and their mother
will be able to listen in.

37
00:02:06.418 --> 00:02:09.318
All right! Turn off
the building's electromagnetic shield!

38
00:02:14.635 --> 00:02:16.470
All teams. comms are open!

39
00:02:16.804 --> 00:02:17.763
Go for breach!

40
00:02:28.107 --> 00:02:29.316
What's going on?

41
00:02:31.694 --> 00:02:33.946
You let the likes of Public Security
surround us?

42
00:02:34.029 --> 00:02:35.114
You fools!

43
00:02:45.583 --> 00:02:46.959
Stay where you are!

44
00:02:47.626 --> 00:02:49.276
Who gave the order to open fire?!

45
00:02:51.005 --> 00:02:52.214
Hold it!

46
00:02:55.426 --> 00:02:56.719
And what do we have here?

47
00:02:56.802 --> 00:02:58.805
If it isn't the Far East
Trade Representative.

48
00:02:58.888 --> 00:03:01.432
the Vice-Minister of Commerce.
and an Executive of the union.

49
00:03:01.724 --> 00:03:03.601
Oh. it's just you. Aramaki.

50
00:03:03.684 --> 00:03:08.230
This will finally give me enough evidence
to send you packing to your home country.

51
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:11.066
I wouldn't count my chickens
so fast if I were you.

52
00:03:11.275 --> 00:03:14.325
Shall I have you sit in
on his deposition. Vice-Minister Ito?

53
00:03:14.486 --> 00:03:16.322
Just to make sure I have
a detailed account

54
00:03:16.405 --> 00:03:19.367
regarding the bombing that killed
the late Prime Minister

55
00:03:19.450 --> 00:03:21.410
and who leaked the conference location.

56
00:03:21.702 --> 00:03:23.037
It's all over…

57
00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:25.498
I'm afraid that won't
be possible. Aramaki.

58
00:03:25.581 --> 00:03:28.125
The Vice-Minister
will be joining me on my flight.

59
00:03:28.626 --> 00:03:30.920
His request for asylum
has been granted.

60
00:03:31.003 --> 00:03:32.672
and I have a signed affidavit. too.

61
00:03:32.755 --> 00:03:33.589
When?!

62
00:03:33.672 --> 00:03:35.622
I'm under no obligation to answer that.

63
00:03:35.883 --> 00:03:38.970
Under international law.
I have the authority to take him

64
00:03:39.053 --> 00:03:41.013
into protective custody and take him home.

65
00:03:41.096 --> 00:03:43.391
Then in accordance with
international anti-terrorism laws.

66
00:03:43.474 --> 00:03:44.892
we request his extradition!

67
00:03:45.392 --> 00:03:47.937
When the paperwork arrives.
we'll consider it.

68
00:03:48.354 --> 00:03:51.154
Mark my words. Vice-Minister.
you'll be killed for this.

69
00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:56.153
My country is a civilized.
pacifist nation.

70
00:03:57.279 --> 00:03:58.489
Oh. is it now?

71
00:03:58.572 --> 00:03:59.448
Wha…

72
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:04.008
Utilizing low-velocity.
soft-point explosive bullets

73
00:04:11.919 --> 00:04:12.962
Outside the window!

74
00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:15.047
There's nothing on the sensors!

75
00:04:28.644 --> 00:04:31.063
Is that 2902 thermal optical camo?!

76
00:04:31.730 --> 00:04:33.280
Go get a tracker!
- Yes. sir!

77
00:04:40.698 --> 00:04:42.032
Here's the tracker. sir.

78
00:04:42.825 --> 00:04:44.368
It's too late.

79
00:04:48.831 --> 00:04:52.627
The next day. that woman appeared at
the Minister of Internal Affairs' office.

80
00:04:52.710 --> 00:04:56.296
a kill order signed by the former
Prime Minister in her hand.

81
00:04:57.715 --> 00:04:59.508
This woman. who gave her name
as "Motoko Kusanagi."

82
00:04:59.591 --> 00:05:01.719
proposed the formal creation
of a new special forces unit.

83
00:05:01.802 --> 00:05:03.702
citing the need for crisis management.

84
00:05:04.054 --> 00:05:06.807
That same day. the Minister of Internal
Affairs summoned Daisuke Aramaki.

85
00:05:06.890 --> 00:05:11.020
requesting that he devise a plan
to bring her into Public Security.

86
00:05:11.103 --> 00:05:13.105
Aramaki agrees.

87
00:05:13.188 --> 00:05:20.154
People like her. you need to keep
on a tight leash.

88
00:05:20.654 --> 00:05:25.242
She requested the formation
of a special forces unit.

89
00:05:25.325 --> 00:05:27.244
Just like you did.

90
00:07:01.964 --> 00:07:03.841
APRIL 10. 2029

91
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:12.891
Major. We got a job. Meet up with "Suisen"
in South Niihama Ward 4.

92
00:07:13.559 --> 00:07:15.352
Funny. I don't remember
signing a contract.

93
00:07:15.561 --> 00:07:17.938
No contract. no deal!

94
00:07:18.397 --> 00:07:21.442
The budget you requested to set up
your pet special forces unit

95
00:07:21.525 --> 00:07:23.194
was just passed by the National Council.

96
00:07:23.277 --> 00:07:25.362
Fuchikoma!
Check the public record!

97
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:26.530
Yessir!

98
00:07:28.782 --> 00:07:31.660
Don't moan like that. damn it!
It grosses me out.

99
00:07:31.743 --> 00:07:35.539
An audio implant I had installed
the other day has a loose connection.

100
00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:36.957
So what's up?

101
00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:40.002
You're really going through
with this deal with Public Security?

102
00:07:40.085 --> 00:07:42.505
If I'm gonna set up
an official special forces unit.

103
00:07:42.588 --> 00:07:44.590
I can't do it without the Bureau's help.

104
00:07:44.673 --> 00:07:48.094
That outfit's chief is no dummy.
We'll get swallowed up by Public Security.

105
00:07:48.177 --> 00:07:53.223
Report located confirming passage
of budget by the 327th National Council!

106
00:07:54.391 --> 00:07:55.225
Well…

107
00:07:56.185 --> 00:07:59.730
I guess that means
he wasn't lying about that. anyway.

108
00:08:00.522 --> 00:08:03.567
Okay! Our round-the-clock
cherry blossom observation is canceled!

109
00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:04.943
Let's go to work!

110
00:08:05.402 --> 00:08:07.529
I thought I was gonna die of boredom.

111
00:08:08.864 --> 00:08:11.242
Okay. people. stand by to brain-dive.

112
00:08:11.325 --> 00:08:13.160
We'll get tapped if we do it on comms.

113
00:08:13.243 --> 00:08:15.746
Do you want a sit-rep
before we get there or not?

114
00:08:15.829 --> 00:08:16.831
I'll use an attack barrier

115
00:08:16.914 --> 00:08:19.542
created by a wizard cyberbrain tech
to keep the hackers away.

116
00:08:19.625 --> 00:08:21.627
It's a hardcore type
that kills the hacker.

117
00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:25.172
When you feel a tingle. that's
my Ghost line. Don't dive past there.

118
00:08:25.255 --> 00:08:26.506
Yeah. fine.

119
00:08:39.478 --> 00:08:42.228
That brain of yours is in serious
need of decluttering.

120
00:08:42.564 --> 00:08:45.276
Wow. Major. your prosthetic hands
are killing you. huh?

121
00:08:45.359 --> 00:08:48.445
What's this bitter taste I'm getting?
Some kind of sedative?

122
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:50.197
You got the intel for the op. right?

123
00:08:50.280 --> 00:08:53.117
If you're not out of my head in two
seconds. I'll fry your brain cells!

124
00:08:53.200 --> 00:08:56.703
I can't believe those clowns
dove that close to my damn Ghost.

125
00:08:57.329 --> 00:09:02.084
This is why I hate letting a bunch of
insensitive jerks into my brain!

126
00:09:05.254 --> 00:09:06.547
SOUTH NIIHAMA WARD 4

127
00:09:06.630 --> 00:09:08.382
"Suisen" Field Command Post / Ground
Crew: 2 / Command Post Admin Robot: 1

128
00:09:08.465 --> 00:09:11.218
SOUTH NIIHAMA CULTURAL CENTER

129
00:09:16.181 --> 00:09:17.849
So. what's the situation?

130
00:09:19.309 --> 00:09:22.229
Public Security currently has
the Sacred Citizen Relief Center

131
00:09:22.312 --> 00:09:23.856
under round-the-clock surveillance.

132
00:09:23.939 --> 00:09:25.232
Relief center?

133
00:09:25.315 --> 00:09:27.484
It's a welfare facility
that takes in war orphans.

134
00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:30.404
and provides them with a home. education.
and work opportunities.

135
00:09:30.487 --> 00:09:33.741
If that's the case. it has nothing
to do with us. Buh-bye.

136
00:09:33.824 --> 00:09:36.493
They have a Ghost controller. Major!

137
00:09:36.660 --> 00:09:37.828
Whoa. old school.

138
00:09:37.911 --> 00:09:39.788
To boost the effectiveness
of the brainwashing.

139
00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:42.541
they also appear to be developing
a new type of Ghost key.

140
00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:45.252
You had a hacker poke around
and they came up empty. huh?

141
00:09:45.335 --> 00:09:47.087
So. what? Steal it? Kill them?

142
00:09:47.212 --> 00:09:48.422
Nothing of the sort!

143
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:52.050
Your objective is to subdue them
if necessary and arrest them.

144
00:09:52.175 --> 00:09:54.136
Without any evidence or a warrant?

145
00:09:54.219 --> 00:09:55.969
We got a hit. that much is certain!

146
00:09:56.805 --> 00:10:00.600
Is their plan to bait me into attacking
the place and then go after me in court?

147
00:10:00.851 --> 00:10:02.019
Hell if I know.

148
00:10:02.853 --> 00:10:03.895
Sheesh!

149
00:10:04.438 --> 00:10:07.233
Doing half-assed stuff like this
won't get us anywhere.

150
00:10:07.316 --> 00:10:09.234
Is Ape-face trying to sabotage me?

151
00:10:10.986 --> 00:10:16.158
The relief center
is a happy. happy place!

152
00:10:16.241 --> 00:10:21.288
The teachers are oh so nice!

153
00:10:21.663 --> 00:10:24.082
The meals are the best.

154
00:10:24.374 --> 00:10:25.668
The beds are soft as clouds!

155
00:10:25.751 --> 00:10:27.086
And even the work is fun!

156
00:10:27.169 --> 00:10:32.632
We're so lucky to get
rice gruel every day!

157
00:10:34.468 --> 00:10:36.970
We humbly thank you. School-Master!

158
00:10:37.137 --> 00:10:40.140
Thank you so very much!

159
00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:41.641
Eat up!

160
00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:56.282
If you don't like it. don't eat it!

161
00:10:56.365 --> 00:10:57.949
All of you. get to work!

162
00:10:58.992 --> 00:11:00.577
Work for the food you ate!

163
00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:03.497
The bed you slept in!
And the work we give you!

164
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:11.630
That looks painful.

165
00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:14.591
Why isn't the Human Rights Bureau
doing anything?

166
00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:17.636
If you don't want to work.
go to the learning course!

167
00:11:17.719 --> 00:11:21.014
And if you don't want to do either one.
I won't apply you for a Citizen's Card!

168
00:11:21.348 --> 00:11:22.933
They got him too. huh?

169
00:11:23.016 --> 00:11:25.102
I hope he can take what they dish out.

170
00:11:25.352 --> 00:11:27.312
Do you have a feed
from the learning course?

171
00:11:27.562 --> 00:11:28.897
Sorry. no.

172
00:11:28.980 --> 00:11:30.690
No?!

173
00:11:31.066 --> 00:11:34.820
Major. I'm sending you a feed
from the learning course on line four.

174
00:12:01.763 --> 00:12:03.766
The universe is falling on me!

175
00:12:03.849 --> 00:12:06.935
Hey! You're overflowing to the others!
Calm down!

176
00:12:07.018 --> 00:12:08.687
I can't take it anymore!

177
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:16.945
It's just a plain old education device!

178
00:12:17.028 --> 00:12:19.782
Don't yank my chain!
"Ghost controller." my ass!

179
00:12:19.865 --> 00:12:21.825
Hang on.
They've dispatched security to get him.

180
00:12:21.908 --> 00:12:23.202
Yeah. so what?

181
00:12:23.285 --> 00:12:24.912
Just before the feed cut out.

182
00:12:24.995 --> 00:12:28.445
didn't you feel like. "If they catch me.
at least it'll all be over"?

183
00:12:29.666 --> 00:12:33.003
Togusa! Ishikawa! Plant the runaway kid
with a baby spider.

184
00:12:33.170 --> 00:12:34.212
On it.

185
00:12:35.505 --> 00:12:40.302
"If this goes sideways. you can retire
and the unit will go on." huh?

186
00:12:40.886 --> 00:12:44.431
I wouldn't get off that easy.
I appreciate the thought. though.

187
00:12:51.771 --> 00:12:55.067
Look. Ishikawa…
I've got a bad feeling about this.

188
00:12:55.150 --> 00:12:56.944
Suck it up. Newbie.

189
00:12:57.027 --> 00:13:00.614
That female-ape has our balls
in her mighty grip.

190
00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:01.990
My hearing's mighty. too.

191
00:13:02.282 --> 00:13:06.203
How lucky we are to have such a young
and beautiful and kind squad leader!

192
00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:07.120
Good.

193
00:13:22.844 --> 00:13:24.888
Circle around and head him off.

194
00:13:24.971 --> 00:13:25.889
Yes. sir.

195
00:13:31.603 --> 00:13:35.357
This guard will be in sleep mode
for 25 seconds. Newbie.

196
00:13:35.524 --> 00:13:38.568
Give the "Newbie" crap a rest!
I'm on it!

197
00:13:59.214 --> 00:14:00.465
Major.

198
00:14:00.674 --> 00:14:02.050
The guards here

199
00:14:02.133 --> 00:14:06.096
are some seriously modified
Sagawa Heavy Industries type 2033s.

200
00:14:06.179 --> 00:14:08.724
Those are custom jobs used
by the military in artillery squads.

201
00:14:08.807 --> 00:14:11.477
They're just back-alley chop shop cyborgs
using that same model.

202
00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:14.563
They're also using government-issue
fiber optic nerves.

203
00:14:14.813 --> 00:14:17.816
That means that
they're on the government's payroll.

204
00:14:17.983 --> 00:14:21.111
Are you sure you didn't get hit
with a simulated experience?

205
00:14:21.486 --> 00:14:24.614
My barrier is no cheap piece of junk.

206
00:14:25.115 --> 00:14:28.035
Either way. it'll be a scandal
if we storm the place.

207
00:14:28.118 --> 00:14:31.455
Who's gonna be the one to take the heat?
Some politician?

208
00:14:31.538 --> 00:14:34.791
Or us? Or those kids?

209
00:14:35.250 --> 00:14:37.461
He must've passed out
from low blood sugar or something.

210
00:14:37.544 --> 00:14:40.547
Too bad. three strikes
and it's brainwashing time.

211
00:14:41.965 --> 00:14:44.301
Sucks to be him.

212
00:14:47.053 --> 00:14:48.972
Get ready to move in. people!

213
00:14:49.472 --> 00:14:52.893
A unit like us is a must in any era.

214
00:14:52.976 --> 00:14:54.811
So we have nothing to lose.

215
00:14:55.145 --> 00:14:56.772
Trying to create a scandal.

216
00:14:56.855 --> 00:14:58.941
Politicians trying
to screw each other over.

217
00:14:59.024 --> 00:15:00.692
Kids being brainwashed.

218
00:15:00.859 --> 00:15:04.863
Rooting out bastards who do this crap
is why I made a deal with Ape-face.

219
00:15:05.280 --> 00:15:07.198
So I say screw it. let's do this.

220
00:15:07.657 --> 00:15:09.951
A little voice is urging me on...

221
00:15:10.243 --> 00:15:12.120
That voice is my Ghost!

222
00:15:18.501 --> 00:15:20.670
Seal off the drainage tunnel ASAP!

223
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:23.089
The kid has a bug on him.

224
00:15:23.632 --> 00:15:25.967
They're onto us!
Togusa. emergency evac!

225
00:15:27.344 --> 00:15:29.721
Switching comms
over to attack barrier mode!

226
00:15:30.347 --> 00:15:32.766
How did they even know
about the drainage tunnel?

227
00:15:32.849 --> 00:15:35.518
Do we have a leak?
Or was this really a trap?

228
00:15:39.648 --> 00:15:42.192
Damage detected in pipe number 17.

229
00:15:42.442 --> 00:15:43.860
You two go check it out.

230
00:15:51.368 --> 00:15:54.418
What are you doing?
You'll get fried by their attack barrier!

231
00:15:54.537 --> 00:15:55.687
I can't. I got locked--

232
00:16:01.044 --> 00:16:03.672
Let's go. Batou.
She was nothing but a speaker.

233
00:16:03.755 --> 00:16:05.299
Public Security will fix her up.

234
00:16:05.382 --> 00:16:08.260
And give her a whole new program
while they're at it?

235
00:16:08.343 --> 00:16:11.054
There's something sad
about these Ghostless puppets.

236
00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:15.100
Especially the type that bleeds red.

237
00:16:17.394 --> 00:16:18.770
That's strange.

238
00:16:18.853 --> 00:16:22.065
I didn't feel that last burst of defiance
you get when a Ghost is fried.

239
00:16:22.148 --> 00:16:24.776
Was it an artificial intelligence
that I roasted?

240
00:16:24.859 --> 00:16:26.111
We're up against pros!

241
00:16:26.820 --> 00:16:28.738
Hey! What's the matter. Togusa?

242
00:16:29.114 --> 00:16:30.157
Togusa!

243
00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:31.950
Togusa! Ow.

244
00:16:32.158 --> 00:16:33.201
Damn it!

245
00:16:33.284 --> 00:16:36.134
This stupid audio implant
with the dumb loose connection!

246
00:16:46.631 --> 00:16:48.481
Hey! Why are you just standing there?

247
00:16:49.092 --> 00:16:50.844
I… I can't go any further.

248
00:16:52.512 --> 00:16:55.432
This is a message
to not throw my life away.

249
00:16:56.015 --> 00:16:58.059
The war is over.

250
00:16:58.184 --> 00:16:59.561
I'm sick of killing people!

251
00:16:59.644 --> 00:17:02.689
Hmph! I'm not a gutless wimp like you!

252
00:17:02.772 --> 00:17:04.190
Fine. Die. then.

253
00:17:16.327 --> 00:17:18.121
Togusa is out cold!

254
00:17:18.204 --> 00:17:19.790
Smack him awake
and get away from there!

255
00:17:19.873 --> 00:17:21.917
To leave?
- To storm the place. obviously!

256
00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:24.961
Our princess
is one hell of a slave driver.

257
00:17:38.725 --> 00:17:40.977
Hang on. that's Ishikawa's Fuchikoma!

258
00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:42.228
What's gotten into him?

259
00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:48.109
Why does his thing have such
a lousy targeting system?

260
00:17:48.359 --> 00:17:50.904
Ishikawa! Snap out of it. damn it!

261
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:57.535
Major! Their security
has a Ghost controller!

262
00:17:58.661 --> 00:18:01.623
Fuchikoma! Close the channel!
Go to lockout mode!

263
00:18:25.772 --> 00:18:28.441
He was able to get in
before my attack barrier could react!

264
00:18:28.608 --> 00:18:29.651
Fuchikoma!

265
00:18:30.193 --> 00:18:33.393
Back-trace his signal path!
Nail his ass with an attack barrier!

266
00:18:33.571 --> 00:18:34.739
Yessir!

267
00:18:40.036 --> 00:18:41.788
You son of a… You'll pay for that!

268
00:18:52.173 --> 00:18:55.385
Having a substitute barrier running
saved my ass.

269
00:18:55.677 --> 00:18:58.513
I have to neutralize
that weird commander of theirs.

270
00:20:01.784 --> 00:20:04.203
No sight. no heat. no sound…

271
00:20:05.246 --> 00:20:07.332
A Kyo-Re Invisibility Cape?!

272
00:20:12.795 --> 00:20:14.505
Okay. enough! I surrender!

273
00:20:14.714 --> 00:20:16.549
Please. just don't damage my brain!

274
00:20:16.883 --> 00:20:19.135
You and me. we're both just doing a job!

275
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:22.138
The Ghost infiltration key
and Ghost controller.

276
00:20:22.221 --> 00:20:23.848
Fine. I'll hand them over!

277
00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:27.519
You're under arrest
for cyberbrain ethics violations.

278
00:20:27.602 --> 00:20:30.021
Are you kidding me?!
You're Public Security?

279
00:20:35.693 --> 00:20:39.656
Y-You came to take us
away from here. right?

280
00:20:39.739 --> 00:20:42.409
Huh? What do you even want?

281
00:20:42.492 --> 00:20:45.078
Are you gonna mooch off of welfare
without meeting your obligations

282
00:20:45.161 --> 00:20:47.246
to society as you're being
brainwashed by trashy media?

283
00:20:47.497 --> 00:20:50.417
At the expense of all the countries
that haven't been as quick to rebuild.

284
00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:52.502
You have a Ghost. too. don't you. kid?

285
00:20:52.669 --> 00:20:56.269
You have a brain in that head of yours.
And you can access a cyberbrain.

286
00:20:59.425 --> 00:21:00.969
Make your own future!

287
00:21:07.392 --> 00:21:11.229
Yes. that was one of the government's
brainwashing facilities.

288
00:21:11.354 --> 00:21:14.804
They were starting to go rogue.
so I had you make an example of them.

289
00:21:15.316 --> 00:21:17.026
The Boss says he wants a word.

290
00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:19.153
I'll transfer you.

291
00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:24.951
Ah. Major Kusanagi. You went
a tad bit overboard. don't you think?

292
00:21:25.034 --> 00:21:27.662
I think you knew that
we would make a mess.

293
00:21:27.745 --> 00:21:32.042
That request I also got from you.
What was it again?

294
00:21:32.125 --> 00:21:35.462
Ah. yes. About the forming of that unit.

295
00:21:35.545 --> 00:21:39.674
When things like this happen…
How can I put this?

296
00:21:39.882 --> 00:21:41.884
It makes things difficult.

297
00:21:42.010 --> 00:21:44.679
Of course. if you were to be
a team player.

298
00:21:45.179 --> 00:21:47.557
perhaps I could find a way
to afford you some leeway.

299
00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:49.142
Give me that Ghost infiltration key.

300
00:21:49.517 --> 00:21:52.771
Mr. Minister? Might I trouble you
for a direct connection for two seconds?

301
00:21:52.854 --> 00:21:54.104
Sure. that would be fine.

302
00:21:58.276 --> 00:22:00.570
If staying here means being
a Public Security errand girl.

303
00:22:00.653 --> 00:22:02.203
I'll find another line of work.

304
00:22:03.364 --> 00:22:04.824
Chief?

305
00:22:07.869 --> 00:22:09.871
I suppose it wasn't meant to be.

306
00:22:13.249 --> 00:22:15.752
Join me for a drink!
Batou. write up the report.

307
00:22:15.835 --> 00:22:16.878
Blech!

308
00:22:16.961 --> 00:22:18.797
Hm? Where'd Togusa go?

309
00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:21.466
After you chewed him out.
he left. bawling his eyes out.

310
00:22:21.549 --> 00:22:23.885
That guy is such a newbie!

311
00:22:24.305 --> 00:23:24.698
